result.execSummary:
Travin Richard Burda was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Travin Richard Burda was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Copy of Waiver of Extradition and Fugitive Complaint forwarded to the Governor of Wisconsin.

Defendant Travin Richard Burda in court, in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court informs defendant in custody out of a Warrant from Wabasha County, MN for charges stated in Fugitive Complaint.  Court explains Extradition process and advises defendant of rights.  Defendant waives extradition.  Waiver of Extradition filed with Court.  Court finds defendant's waiver of extradition done knowingly & voluntarily and remands him to Pepin County Sheriff's Department to forthwith be delivered to Wabasha County, MN.
